Full Description: PeeqMe is an elegantly simple, social, mobile app that puts the user first in talent development and team performance. For the social/knowledge economy, human capital creates the value. The enemy of that is disengagement by people and friction between people. PeeqMe increases engagement through daily interaction with users' own natural gifts, and reduces friction by adding rich, personal context when we work in dispersed and diverse teams.  PeeqMe fills a gap on profiling and collecting 360-feedback on "how" people work, not just what they did/accomplished. PeeqMe creates user profiles from their unique types, based on the most popular personality, behavior, and talent assessments. By focusing on what's special inside, the innate, natural strengths and styles of our users, peeqMe elevates engagement levels. Furthermore, peeqMe allows organizational values and behaviors/competencies to be added to profiles to catch members demonstrating how they work. By relating to their organization's intent, our members get caught demonstrating performance consistent with their affiliated organizations on a continuous cycle by customers, colleagues, management or partners (whether business, service, community, or faith-based). By creating circles of boosters, mentors and coaches, their fresh, frequent, focused feedback empowers our members. Furthermore, in a diverse and dispersed workplace, insights derived from rich but simple profiles reduces team conflicts from misuse and misunderstanding, and drives team performance to higher levels of productivity and innovation.  PeeqMe is the user-driven, follow-me app for personal and professional development. Use it wherever you work... on the job, at home, or in your community.

Full Description: All cc, cash A neuroma is a benign (noncancerous) growth of nerve tissue that can develop in various parts of the body. Morton’s neuroma occurs in a nerve in the foot, often between the third and fourth toes, and involves a thickening of the tissue around one of the nerves leading to the toes. Kesler Podiatry is prepared to offer the best treatment for foot neuroma and Morton’s neuroma for patients in Hawthorne. Morton’s neuroma causes a sharp, burning pain in the ball of the foot. Toes also may sting, burn or feel numb. When walking, it might feel as though there is a pebble in your shoe. People with certain foot deformities such as bunions, hammer toes, flat feet, or more flexible feet are at higher risk for developing a neuroma. Other potential causes are activities that involve repetitive irritation to the ball of the foot, such as running or court sports. An injury or other type of trauma to the area may also lead to a neuroma. Diabetic footwear, sometimes known as “depth shoes,” and custom molded shoe inserts can prevent many foot injuries caused by diabetes. The Medicare Therapeutic Shoe Bill allows qualified persons to receive protective footwear and inserts. This bill was instituted by the federal government to reduce complications associated with diabetes. The staff at our Hawthorne, NJ office is certified and trained to properly fit diabetic patients, mold the inserts, and dispense them to the patient. Properly fitted custom molded inserts and diabetic shoes can assure long-term comfort and decreased risk of complication to your feet from diabetes. Kesler Podiatry proudly offers the area’s best diabetic footwear program to patients in Hawthorne.

Description: Southwest Applied Technology Center is a school in Cedar City.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Southwest Applied Technology Center in Cedar City, Utah offers a unique approach to professional education. What distinguishes Southwest is its open-entry, open-exit model, which allows students to enter at any time. While they are enrolled, they work at a skill for as long as it takes them to gain proficiency and then either move onto the next course or receive a certification based on the skills they have mastered. Students may stop or stay on as long as they want. Certifications at Southwestern go from a Certificate of Skills Competency, which is granted after one course, to the final Certificate of Completion, given to those students who have completed all of the skill-levels in their field. The majors offered at Southwestern train students for such fields as Automotive Technology, Plumbing, Business and Health Careers. In addition to awarding private scholarships and federal grants and loans to eligible students, Southwestern works in collaboration with state and federal organizations such as Department of Workforce Services to help students with certain economic and other challenges.

Description: smart movie recommendations
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: FilmSuggest  helps users find movies they may like based on stated  preferences. FilmSuggest uses the Internet Movie Database (IMDb) to procure titles, genres, actors, directors, plots, and MPAA ratings for each movie. Additionally, FilmSuggest uses Amazon's database for DVD cover artwork and to link to Amazon's store for purchase of DVD titles. The Google Charts API is also used within the site to display users' preference trends in the Profile section of the site. FilmSuggest implements several multi-faceted technologies to function, including cascading style sheets (CSS), asynchronous javascript and XML (AJAX) requests, an open source relational database management system (MySQL), and a server-side cross-platform HTML embedded scripting language (PHP). Crucial frameworks used are the Prototype javascript framework and the Scriptaculous javascript library, which together implement advanced javascript techniques to present and manipulate data. Additionally, Javascript Object Notation (JSON) is used to streamline multi-language information passed between the server and browser.
